A few crows were screaming and swooping down at something and I was wondering what was going on until I noticed there was a fox below, they didn't stop flying above it, swooping down, and cawing until it ran far away, raised an alarm and let everyone in the forest know about it.

This is why everyone respects crows. They get the job done. 2-3 birds managed to notify hundreds of other critters about a predator and single handedly chased the fox away. Shows how useful learning to understand crows is too. Always good info coming from them.

Heavy spoilers ahead, but you can tell Gene Wolfe is an American author because his books are meant to be solved, here the "We were all engendered in women by trees" line in the book reveals the aborigines actually transform into trees as part of their life and reproduction cycle

European novels or films are not really meant to be solved, but Americans naturally engage with art through the "fan theory" concept (what if the Lynch protagonist was actually hallucinating in an insane asylum) and this is how you're meant to read Wolfe. His novels are solvable.

Marc Aramini is the man who solved The Fifth Head of Cerberus aboriginal organism thing, there are a lot of clues in the book about it including characters mentioning their feet feeling stiff or limping as natural processes turn them into trees eventually to be able to reproduce.

There are a few podcasts that go through them and explain them through a theory. Rereading Wolfe podcast is good. I think trying to solve them on your own is impossible back in the day there were huge email groups doing it together

A lot of those more eccentric alt health things like screaming into a pillow and biting your fist or stretching your arms while humming come from Dr. Alexander Lowen's bioenergetics bodywork concepts, a student of Wilhelm Reich's psychoanalysis school.

It's wacky and seems ridiculous when taken out of context (it really is), but Lowen's books and articles and websites dedicated to his work are actually very interesting, it basically involves dissociating sexuality and physical touch to do away with physio-psychosexual pathology
